Create and Use GitHub Personal Access Token

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NV5WPLm0pZs



create PAT for github account
use PAT in git clone command
use PAT for a Git Repo in Eclipse IDE

.PATs are an alternative to using password authentication
.A pat provides more granular access(scopes or permissions)
.PATs can only be used for HTTPS Git operations
.A PAT can have expiration
.From August 13,2021:Github requires PAT when using GitHub API or command line

Why GitHub Personal Access Token???
.Security Benefits:
 -Unique: tokens are specific to GitHub and can be generated per use or per device
 -Revocable:

etc


1 Create a PAT on GitHub

Github user icon -> setting -> Developer setting on left menu-> Personal access tokens -> click Generate new token ->Note(Repo access token) -> Expiration 30days

Programmar want to access repository so in select scopes, give a check "repo" checkbox 
-> click generate token
if so , you will get person access token


